animal.description:
Meet Phineus - in spite of the fact that in his former life someone took a scissor to his ears, this boy is a total lovebug! He is a handsome Doberman mix who's about 4 1/2 years old & weighs 50 pounds! He is a playful pup who will make a great companion! Phineus is up to date on vaccinations and microchipped!! Phineus had a rough start but you would never know it. He loves people and is extremely affectionate and cuddly. He loves to lick your face and loves belly rubs. He loves to be with "his people" and wants to be wherever you are. He is happiest when he is right next to you or in your lap.
He is very food motivated and loves working on his obedience. Phin has already mastered "sit" "down" "paw" "rollover" and "touch" (touch my hand with your nose), "go to bed" (go in his crate). He is pretty good with "stay" "come" and "leave it"
Overall he is very eager to please, motivated by treats/praise and respects "no".

Phin also LOVES toys. He routinely empties the toy bin and scatters bones and toys on the living room floor. He loves to play fetch with himself and fling his stuffed animals across the room and chase after them. He also likes to rip stuffing out and make a mess. He is such a goof ball!
Phin is crate trained and house trained. He is great in the car and on leash. He loves going for walks but does pull when he sees other dogs. Phineus needs to be the only pet in the home.

Children scare Phineus so he should go home to an adult only house.

If you are looking for the most loving, handsome, fun and silly pup to be the utmost loyal companion, this is the boy for you.
If you are interested in meeting with Phineus, be sure to go to our website, EHRDOGS.ORG, and submit an application to adopt or even to foster him!! Don't forget to mention his name, PHINEUS WILSON!!!!

Otis is awesome! He is a very loving boy. He gets along with other dogs but wants to be in charge. He HATES cats. We recommend he be the only pet in the home. He also gets along with children but tries to over power them. We recommend he be in a home with a single person and no children unless in their teens. He definitely needs a chance to be in a furever home! He has been here far too long. 

He is 1 1/2 years old. His current weight is around 45/50 pounds. He is neutered and up to date on vaccines. 

His fee is $150.00. The adoption fee includes the initial vaccines, spay/neuter surgery, microchipping and a deworming. 

We are currently only open by appointment. Due to the recent pandemic, we are looking at the safety of our workers/volunteers that are there to take care of the animals. Only serious inquiries will be considered.

Please visit our website to fill out an application so we can better assist you in your search for your next fur baby.  http://www.achs-pets.com/Application.html 

We are a BEST MATCH facility. We try to match the pet’s personality and needs with the family’s needs and lifestyle to increase the likelihood of a lifetime happy relationship for the whole family. The online application we provide on our website, achs-pets.com, is a preliminary application. After you have completed the application, please give us 3 to 5 business days to process it. We check vaccine records for current & past pets as well as Landlord approval if you do not own your home. We hope you will understand our effort to provide our animals with the best new situation that is possible.

animal.description:
Maya is almost 6 months old, husky mix looking for a forever home! I love her stunning crystal blue eyes and brindle coat. Maya is so goofy and loves to be the boss of everyone. She is a indoor dog who is doing great with the crate training and potty training. Maya is so smart and learning her basic commands. She will become your best friend and your shadow!

We rescued her and bottle fed her at 2 weeks old after someone was selling her on the side of the freeway! I’m so glad she ended up with us! She’s been so fun to foster but now shes ready for her own home. She has all the husky traits and is a talker. Maya has been fully vetted, dewormed, spayed, vaccinated, and microchipped. 

We are looking for a active home locally in Northern California or Sacramento area. Home owners ONLY with a fully fenced in yard that is at least 6 feet tall. No renters or apartments. Must have husky experience! Preferably someone not gone long hours as she’s a needy girl and should would need a home with another doggie playmate. Maya will be a big active breed that will need lots of training and socializing so she’s not for a first time dog owner. No small children as she can easily knock a little one down. 

If you think you are a good fit and are interested in adopting please send us a DETAILED list message about yourself and request a application to fill out. After we review applications we will start setting up interviews and meets. Then home checks with approved applicants. Please be patient with us and we will get back to you at our earliest convenience. Sometimes it can take as least 2-4 weeks. We don’t rush our adoption process and want to find the right match for all our dogs! You can email us at Simbaspawdogrescue@yahoo.com

animal.description:
Bogart is such a handsome boy, with the beautiful coat of a chocolate lab, and the chunky body of a pit bull terrier. In his case, beauty is more than skin deep -- he's sweet, easy-going and playful, He is a volunteer favorite. Bogart came into the shelter as a lost dog on Oct. 17; he was adopted in early November but the family returned him after he got into an altercation with their cat. He loves people, but apparently not cats, so he needs to go to a no-cat household. He is listed as "special needs"  because he  has tested positive for heartworms, and the family that adopts him will need to check with their vet about what treatment he needs. Dogs who are treated for heartworms usually go on to live a happy and playful life; left untreated, heartworms can be fatal. Bogart is about 3 years old and weighs 77 pounds.  He is up-to-date on vaccinations, now neutered and will be microchipped when adopted. Come meet him in Run 85 using ID# 625578. 

Please note, all of the pet listings on Friends of Shelter Animals for Cobb are done by volunteers, not shelter staff. If this pet came in as lost (not an owner surrender), we don't know how they might be with children, other pets, or if house trained. You can bring your pet to the shelter for a meet & greet with your potential new best friend. When calling the shelter about a cat or dog, please use THE ID NUMBER, names are oftentimes made up by volunteers. 

This pet and many others are available for adoption from the Cobb County Animal Shelter 1060 Al Bishop Dr. Marietta, GA 30008, call (770) 499-4136 for more information. Shelter hours are: Tues. - Sun. 10:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. by appointment only until further notice, CLOSED Mondays & Holidays.

animal.description:
"Hey there! My name is Jimmy Chew,  I am around 2 years old, about 40lbs, already neutered, microchipped & up to date on vaccinations and all set to move right into your home and heart! 
  
My friends here describe me as a shy, independent, misunderstood, clever, playful pup. I am most often seen romping in the pens with my jolly ball or taking it on short walks. My friends here think I am funny and a self-entertainer. I am just not always sure how to play with humans, but I love that they like to watch me and laugh. They say I have a lot of puppy-like energy that needs to be channeled into learning and enrichment so that I don't get bored. Give me a rope toy, tennis balls or my favorite jolly ball and watch me go! I am already getting the hang of fun games like “touch” and “find it” but I know that there’s still plenty out there that I’m eager to learn. I am hoping that you will want to teach me too.  
  
I would love a quiet, calm, adult-only home. I’m nervous meeting new people, so I will need my forever humans to go slow and manage interactions safely. I may not be interested in making new friends, so my people will need to accept me for me and not force anything. I am happiest romping in the yard with my toys and friends. I do enjoy our time together and when I am ready, I will give you many kisses like I’ve grown to love to do with my closest friends here at PAC.
  
I’ve also enjoyed making doggie friends at the center and could live with the right dog friend. I love to wrestle and run with my friends and can be a little rough-and-tumble with them, so they have to like that sort of play. With a slow introduction, I might also be able to live with the right kitty roommate - with my type of energy, a cat who is used to this would be best!

So, if you are interested in more information about me and/or would like to set up a meeting with me to get to know me more, please schedule an appointment here: https://providenceac.org/AdoptADog. My paws are crossed I will see you very soon! 

XOXO Jimmy

P.S. Someone is so excited for me to find my fur-ever home, that they have sponsored my adoption fee! That means I can join your family today for FREE! Woohoo!!"

-------
During your appointment, you will be able to meet a selection of pets in the Kennels or Cattery that day. New pets are arriving daily!
-------

Providence Animal Center relies on adoption fees and donations to save pets! Adoption fees vary per pet. To find out this pet’s adoption fee or for more information, please call the Adoption Center with this pet’s ID number.

Can’t adopt? Consider fostering or donating! Visit https://providenceac.org/support-us/ for more information on how you can support the lifesaving mission!

Bonnie walks nicely on her leash and is learning how to properly greet her neighbors and fellow pups.  She has learned "sit" and "wait" and will need continued training but responds well to treats, so she'll be quick learning other commands.

animal.description:
Approved applicants can meet AllyMae in her foster home. She needs a home without children.  A home with another dog friendly dog is a must. Please read all about her below. 

Adoption coordinator Kathy

Meet AllyMae! She’s 2.5 yrs old and weighs about 60 lbs. She came into rescue as part of a dog cruelty seizure and was kept in a 4x8 pen in very unsanitary conditions. She is a high energy dog and is very true to her breed. She will bay loudly when she catches a scent. She needs a cat free home.  She’s house trained and ok in a crate and on a leash, but must be walked with a thick rope type leash as if she bolts after a scent she can snap a thinner leash. A fenced yard is best, but her current foster is managing her without one. She can likely climb a chain link fence. She’ll need plenty of exercise. She is not a good fit for an apartment. Because of her loud coonhound bark, she’d do best in a neighborhood where houses are spaced a good distance apart or a more rural setting. She loves other dogs, so a home with another dog to play with is a must.  Her current foster is enjoying her very much. He describes her as loving, easy going and very trainable. He said she loves people, other dogs and enjoys long walks and playing. She is a GREAT dog for someone who loves a hound dog!! Adoption fee $300. 




Please complete an online APPLICATION if you wish to adopt.  Forever Home Rescue New England is a 501(c)3  non-profit organization. We are a network of foster homes in the South and the New England area. THERE IS NO SPECIFIC SHELTER LOCATION. If you wish to meet our dogs, you must first be approved by going through our application and screening process. Forever Home Rescue suggests obedience training for all puppies and dogs. All dogs are up to date on their shots, dewormed and spayed or neutered. Vet fees, transport fee and New England quarantine fees ARE INCLUDED in each dog's adoption fee. Also, any dogs older than pups--even if they are not marked housetrained in their posting---usually housetrain within a day or two, because most are used to living outside in the south and will prefer to do their business outdoors. Our dogs and pups are best suited for families with children 5 yrs old and up. If you are approved to adopt, please submit the $100 deposit by clicking on our rescue's name in this posting (Forever Home Rescue New England--in purple) which will bring you to a new page with the deposit link at the bottom.  STOP! If you have not been notified of your approval status do not make a deposit.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Clay County Animal Rescue & Shelter is located at 14400 Hwy. 45 in Louisville, IL. Our phone number is 618-665-3005. The shelter is open to the public 1-3 Monday-Saturday. Sundays we are open 1-4 to the public. If those times don't work, please call to set up a time to visit.

The typical adoption fee for dogs is $150. It includes vaccination, deworming , spay/neuter, heartworm testing on dogs of age and microchipping, which is now mandatory by state law. Some dogs we discount to as little as $50 due to sponsorship. Some dogs we ask a higher adoption fee, which helps us recoup expenses on heartworm treatment on other dogs.

All cats are spayed/neutered/vaccinated/flea treated/dewormed and microchipped prior to adoption. Cat adoption fees range from $60-$100. We spay/neuter/microchip/vaccinate and deworm all kittens and cats, prior to adoption. Our shyer/less adoptable cats are classed as "barn cats" and are free with a completed/approved barn cat application, which can be found on our website.

For updates on adoption events and more pics of pets available, go to our website, www.claycountyshelter.com or look for us on Facebook.

animal.description:
Meet Ellie Mae! 

Ellie May is a very sweet and loving girl, and she bonds quickly. Her general behavior is exemplary - no accidents or chewing for this girl! She is a five year old, 45 lb Australian shepherd mix, with soft luxurious fur, and beautiful half-and-half face markings.

Because Ellie is a "working" breed, she has different needs than an average dog. She requires confident, calm leadership. She will definitely do best with an experienced owner. Familiarity with her breed's characteristics is a plus. She is pack-oriented, and needs a leader to help her understand her status, especially where children and other pets are concerned. Without consistent, positive training, she will not acclimate well to a household with other pets or children. Because of this, she probably needs to go to a home with no children. She does well in her foster home, so experienced owners with pets can be considered. Ellie currently lives with a non-dominant dog and a large, dog savvy cat. She is learning to be respectful of them, and is doing extremely well, but it has required a fair amount of effort and training. With time, Ellie is learning to relax and just enjoy being part of the family, but it has been an adjustment for her, and for her pet siblings. Ellie is extremely intelligent and learns quickly, which is typical of her breed. She just needs someone who understands how to communicate with her, and can show her what is expected of her.

Ellie generally walks well on a loose leash, but her protective instincts kick in if a person, other dog, or car passes. She is particularly reactive to delivery trucks! She is working on this, and will need someone to continue this training with her. 

Contrary to her breed, Ellie is not terribly high energy, and does not require a lot of exercise. She does require mental stimulation, so some shorter walks throughout the day would work well for her. Training sessions, play time and puzzles will also help. A fenced yard would be a plus. Ellie does sometimes dig, but it's usually to dig up a tasty grub, rather than an effort to escape. Ellie can be trusted to be left alone indoors without being destructive, but she is currently being secluded in a separate bedroom, as she needs to be supervised with other household pets. Ellie does occasionally bark at outside noises, people, etc. but it has lessened over time, as she realizes that she does not need to be in charge.

Ellie does not show guarding around her food dish, but she instinctively shows a lot of interest around food in general. Her new family will need to establish clear rules with Ellie about food. She is being taught "Down/Stay" during family mealtimes, and is doing very well with it. 

In the right home, Ellie is a joyful, goofy girl. She absolutely loves her toys, going for walks, snuggling, belly rubs, and sitting outside in the sun. She does not tend to "herd" people as many dogs of her breed. One of her charming quirks is that she follows closely behind people as they walk around the home, usually with a toy in her mouth, ever so lightly pressed against the back of the person's legs. It's really adorable! Ellie is also talkative when she needs something. She will have a "chat" with you if she needs a potty break, and can give a sassy little bark or grumble if she's asked to do something she's not a fan of.

Ellie is spayed, microchipped, fully vetted, and up-to-date on vaccinations and monthly flea/tick and heart worm preventatives. If you have questions about Ellie May, you can email her foster at Deb@pawsforlifenc.org. If you think Ellie May is a good match for you, you can fill in an online application for here at www.pawsforlifenc.org. 

As part of Ellie Mae's $250 adoption fee, she is spayed, microchipped, up to date on vaccines, and current on her monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. Ellie Mae is heartworm negative. If you have questions about this sweet girl, you can email Dogteam@pawsforlifenc.org. If you wish to adopt Ellie Mae, you can fill in an online application for her under the Adopt a Pet Tab on our website: www.pawsforlifenc.org.

Norma Jean is a 10 year old yellow lab mixed with a chihuahua. She weighs about 25 lbs and is super sweet and gentle.  She would be considered a special needs baby. When she was brought into the shelter, she mostly likely had been hit by a car.  She had full hip and hind end X-rays done and she is in perfect health structurally, no arthritis.  She also had a recent blood panel and she has the blood of a puppy.  The vet believes that she has a neurological problem that causes her to not always know right away when she is dedicating.  She sometimes is able to run outside and other times she can’t make it.  Luckily, she doesn’t make a mess at all and her foster says it’s super easy to just pick up.  Norma Jean loves all dogs and cats.  She would love to cuddle with you or relax on her bed.  She enjoys resting in the sunny backyard and snacking on yummy treats.  Norma is spayed, micro chipped and up to date on all shots.

animal.description:
Meet Cooper. This guy was rescued off a chain by one of our volunteers. He was allowed indoors as a small puppy and then let roam for awhile. The last few months he spent his life on a chain. Thankfully, his family had no issue surrendering him to us. We were told he is a Lab/Husky mix and that he was born in Feb 2020. He had his first vet visit and weighed 63 lbs. Cooper is a very sweet boy and has made great progress since he’s been with his foster. He does have some Husky traits. He can be a little weary with strangers and need a little patience. We have learned if you don’t pay attention to him and let him come to you at his own pace he does much better. He also can be vocal at times especially if other dogs are. He also has some labby traits. He’s goofy and has no idea of his size. He’s also playful and super loving. Both breeds are energetic as is he. He enjoys playing with toys, other dogs, running in the yard and taking walks. He does well with other dogs but proper intros are a must. He is house and kennel trained. He loves his fosters grandkids. He loves toys, cuddling on the couch and snoozing in the bed with you. He’s walking great on a harness and his foster is working hard to break his jumping when excited. He’s very eager to please and will make a great pet for someone willing to put in the time with this boy. He is utd, hw neg (tested below detectable levels) and neutered! 

All dogs have a $175 adoption fee which includes vet check, age appropriate shots (atleast 2 sets for puppies), dewormer, heartworm test (if over 6 months), rabies (if atleast 16 weeks) and spay/neuter! Puppies will be altered before adoption. All rescues and shelters practice pediatric spay and neuter. This is essential in our rescue efforts and it is a policy that we will stick by. All dogs over 8 weeks and 2 pounds will be altered before adoption. There are no exceptions to this rule on all healthy and adoptable dogs. 

Puppies/Dogs that are not available for adoption due to vetting not being complete can be reserved with an approved application and a non refundable $50 deposit. This deposit is applied to your adoption fee and the remaining $125 is due at pick up.

Wags and Whiskers is an all-volunteer rescue. We also have full-time jobs and Families. We will try to answer all questions and applications in a timely manner. Please be patient and bear with us . Do not contact Parkway Animal Hospital as they are a vet clinic and can not answer questions on behalf of Wags and Whiskers. All questions and comments must go directly through the rescue. Thank you for your understanding.

ADOPTION APPLICATION

animal.description:
Have you ever seen a miniature German shepherd? Once you meet Felix you can check that off your list! Because at a whole 30 pounds, this 3yo looks like a shrunken German Shepherd Dog!

What Felix lacks in size he makes up for in personality! This goofball wants to be your own personal shadow - following you everywhere, giving you kisses when you bend down, picking up food you accidentally dropped. Hes the perfect sidekick because hes right by your side and doesnt want to miss out on any of the action. In his foster home he has thrived with structure and routine and has become the ultimate cuddle buddy!

In order to enjoy this side of Felix, he will need an adopter(s) who is extremely patient and understand that building a relationship with Felix will take time! Rome wasnt built in a day, nor will Felixs trust happen overnight. Felix is slow to trust and warm up to new people but oh boy, if youre fortunate enough to get on his good side he will shower you with love and affection! In fact, hell shower you with the love and affection he seems to have been denied prior to having been rescued!

Felix would do best in a home that could continue to reinforce his training. Felix is a graduate of Golden Heart Canines board and train program which means hes got the skills to loose leash walk and knows commands like sit, wait, down, stay, and place. He has also recently learned how to shake!

While on a leash, Felix walks with a loose leash and loves to be outside! Sometimes he gets distracted by bunnies and squirrels but a quick correction and he comes back to the expected behavior. He would be an excellent hiking partner too! In his Texas foster home, Felix was taken on daily runs. A walk seems to tire him out just fine though so no need for only marathon runners to apply.

Felix does appreciate slower introductions to other dogs but once theyre buddies, theres no stopping play time! Felix loves to play chase and tag with other dogs and he likes to boop other dogs. Weve tested Felix with bigger dogs, smaller dogs, mellow dogs, hyper dogs, and puppies and hes done great with all of them - he just likes a proper doggie handshake before jumping in to play. We would encourage Felix be adopted into a home with another confident dog because Felix warms up to people significantly quicker if he is around dogs who model good interactions with people.

Felix is crate trained, potty trained, and is overall a very quiet and well behaved dog. Felix LOVES his crate and he can frequently be found sleeping in his crate with the door wide open. He enjoys the company of the other dogs in his foster home and frequently initiates playtime with the dogs. When his foster siblings are tired out and refuse to play anymore, Felix will grab a toy from the toy bin and entertain himself by throwing his toy in the air and trying to catch it.

Felix likely hasn't spent much time inside a home prior to his foster home because things like the dishwasher running and the toilet flushing are a little scary. Because hes easily startled we do not recommend a home with kids for Felix.

He's been working on his confidence and learning how to dog by playing with toys and going to breweries but hes still got a ways to go. Even though Felix has been visiting breweries, hes been muzzled and in controlled situations, but this is not where Felix thrives. Felix will thrive in a quiet home without a lot of action OR in a home that understands that meeting new people can and does stress him out, so hell need to be crated or muzzled when new people come to his home.

Felix is a fantastic dog and just needs someone to take a chance on him. We know Felixs forever human(s) is around the corner and we cant wait to help him find it!

**Please note that due to Felix's need to build trust and relationships over time, he will require 5+ meet and greets before he can be added to your home.**

**Homeownership required**

Felix makes his bed: https://youtu.be/8b-036QW1XA

Playing with Forrest: https://youtu.be/PQClb5RvaNA

*HOME OWNERSHIP REQUIRED!*

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
BACKSTORY:
A bunch of dogs were surrendered to an area animal control when a family came on hard times and could no longer care for them, none of the dogs were bonded, they were just housemates even though 3 of them were related. This entire bunch was under socialized, never walked on leash, and had a hard time navigating the outside world. Our hearts absolutely broke and we made it our mission to get them into foster care where they could be surrounded by love and dedicated people who would help them learn to be successful companions, but more importantly to be dogs. Two such foster families stepped up to be those people!

Boba's foster family is working to help build his confidence, and lessen his anxieties as well as helping him learn the manners he was never taught.

EDUCATION:
* Sit
* Paw
* Touch
* Is starting to get place and down
* Doesn't beg at the dinner table
* Can play on his own
* He does very well being left out in a gated area in the house
ACTIVITIES THIS CUTIE ENJOYS:
* Treats: cod skins, peanut butter, hot dogs, Zuke's training treats, chicken
* Food: he loves to eat!
* Toys: loves toys!
* Walks: he enjoys long walks in the woods and is excellent on leash
* Running in the yard
* Training sessions
* Snuggling
* Loves being in the car and he travels well
* Hanging out on restaurant patios with people
* Ear, chin, and belly scratches
* Zoomies
* He enjoys attention and affection
* Sleeping in people beds and on couches
SKILLS:
* Dogs: friendly, excited, he's a little awkward with dogs when playing
* Kids: friendly but we recommend kids 10+ years or older
* People: friendly, excited, warms up to women more quickly
* Cats: unknown

CHALLENGES:
* Learning to love his crate but he does great when he is gated off instead
* Can be mouthy when excited but settles down
* He has been known to jump
* Has some separation anxiety
* Recommend a home where someone is home most of the time
* He will follow you everywhere
* We recommend a fenced yard
* Not a fan of baths
* He seeks affirmations and attention all the livelong day

animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in dog who needs a new home. Adoption can be one of the most fulfilling experiences in your life and especially in the life of your new canine companion.

A note to those looking at CPR. We have no perfect dogs - but many of our dogs have proven to be perfect for a certain someone. Our job is to find those someone's. Our most successful adopters come to CPR not because they want a dog. They come to us because they want to give a dog a home. We urge all of our potential adopters not to fall in love with a picture. While we like to know what you like in looks, a dog is more than a pretty face. Our goal is to match you with the best possible pet for you and your home. We want to create furever families.

Our descriptions contain all that we know about this dog today. We'll update as more information is known.

Are you looking to adopt within the next 30 days? If so please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and complete the application. You'll find it in the menu on the left hand side. You'll also find a total listing of all our dogs available.

Just browsing but interested in poodles and poodle mixes? Please drop a note to applications@carolinapoodlerescue.org with your name, address and phone # and email. We'll add you to our mailing list.

thanks
the CPR Adoption team

Date into Rescue: 10/10/2020
Reason for being in rescue: stray
Foster location: Dreamweaver Farms, Pacolet SC
Special Needs? none
Weight: 15.5 lbs and growing. We expect Stacy will be between 25-30 pounds when she is full grown.
Height: 9 in
Spayed/Neutered: Yes, Stacy Dirk was spayed on 10/20/2020. She is ready for her forever home.

Adoption Fee: $200

Fence needed? Yes

What kind of home would be best for me? Stacy Dirk is a happy, very active puppy. She would be best in a home with another active dog and someone home during the day for physical and mental exercise. Stacy is learning the ropes of being a pet, but needs continued training on basic manners, house training, and walking on a leash. She would be wonderful for mature children (no children under 10 as she is very much a puppy and still chews... puppy teeth are sharp). She needs a fenced yard where she can run out her energy and play ball with her family every day. Stacy Dirk would love to be your hiking buddy!

What is my personality like? Stacy Dirk was abandoned behind a convenience store. Thankfully, the manager on duty is a dog lover and scooped this baby girl up. We cannot imagine how or why someone could abandon a young girl as full of personality and life as Stacy Dirk. But her past will not define her future.

Stacy Dirk is your classic happy, very active puppy. She loves everyone she wants to meet and is always up for an adventure. She's living in a foster home with other dogs that are small and large and does well with them. We don't recommend a home with cats as Stacy is just too curious and energetic for your average cat.

Stacy Dirk is learning all sorts of things in her foster home. First up was crate training. She's done very well with that and sleeps in her crate quietly at night. She is learning to walk on a leash, though she sometimes think it's a chew toy while she's walking. She knows basic command (sit and down) and is working on the leave it command. She absolutely loves toys, loves people, and is wide open energy all the time.

How do I act when I first meet new people? Very friendly

Other tips and tidbits: Stacy Dirk's estimated birthday is 6/10/2020

House trained? Dogs can be house trained if they are in the right environment and are allowed to follow a schedule as long as a physical reason doesn't keep them from being trained. A dog house trained in my home may not be in yours. We will help you teach your new dog this necessary skill and based on your schedule.

Please note - we do not ship dogs. If you are interested in adopting, please take a look at the distance between the foster home location and your location and make sure you are willing to make that trip. Most of our dogs are at our farm in Pacolet, South Carolina.

To apply, please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and visit the tab on the left that directions you to the online application.

Please note that when screening applications, we look at the entire home and then make suggestions based on what would be a good fit for your home. You are not being screened for a specific dog although we are looking to see what type of dog interests you - poodles or non poodles, color, age, etc. Others here may be a better fit for you. It is very difficult to get to know a living animal from a picture and a short description. Since we are constantly getting in new dogs, this may be a dog not in our listings yet. We want you to be very happy with your new companion and will make suggestions based on what you tell us about you.

Thank you for considering CPR.

animal.description: This is Hugo Hugo is a good boy but not suitable for a home with small animals or children under 16, He needs a dominant assertive owner who will be able to teach him the manners he so desperately needs. He knows sit, but is an extremely high energy dog, he would need lots of exercise and would not be suitable for an apartment setting. We were lucky enough to get some insight from his previous adopter and this is what she had to say: he's very sweet and he's so nice, but he does have a lot of energy. I would say he really likes pets and being on the couch. Couches are his favorite and he'll gladly rest on your lap if you let him. He has a nipping problem but he doesn't mean to hurt. He enjoyed Kraft Cheese. We gave him squeaky toys and those were his favorites and so were Kong toys, especially if you put peanut butter on them. Running is good for him and he knows how to sit. I would say give him a harness instead of a leash because he will pull. He loves people, but he didn't seem to be a fan of little kids. He's a quick learner, very sweet. And the sun was his favorite thing to sleep in. We've noticed on walks when he can see his own image, he didn't like looking at him. And windy days, when something would flap loudly, it would startle him. Watch the coffee mugs around his wagging tail, though, that's powerful. Hugo is one of the dogs that has been at our shelter for the longest, although we love him we are so desperate to see him in his forever home where he can get the training, excercise and the love that he so much longs for. If you are interested in Hugo please call our adoptions line at 301-780-7201.

animal.description:
Meet Domino, a 77lb American Bulldog/Pitbull Mix believed to be around 5-6 years old. Domino is a total sweetheart who makes any day better by just being his goofy self! He loves his people, walks, naps, and bringing you his toys when you come home. Domino was believed to be a victim of a dog attack as his bite wounds were consistent with a gnarly dog on dog encounter where he did not have the upper paw. His foster family believes that's the reason why he is extremely cautious of big dogs. Although he wouldn't mind being in home where he is your one and only, following a slow and proper introduction, Domino does great with smaller submissive dogs. He also sometimes gets overwhelmed with fast, quick movements, so an easy-going adult home with no children will make him happiest. Despite his size, Domino is a true gentleman on leash, who makes many human friends on his walks. He is a super quick learner who is house broken and crate trained, and already knows several commands.. He has also learned to politely wait for his food. To see Domino being the best boy in his foster home, follow him @spikemontgomerythepibble on Instagram!

This animal's adoption fee is $200

I like lay on the rug in the lobby and tare the tennis balls to shreds and then get a new one. I have basic listening skills, sometimes I ignore the humans when they are trying to get me to listen. They always want me to do things that are boring like get in my kennel. I always sit when they bring me my food. I'll do just about anything if your gonna give me food. One time I got out of my kennel and followed one of my humans to the dumpster and helped her take the garbage out and then I followed her back to the building and went back inside without a leash. I'm a good boy like that.

animal.description:
…...unfortunately we can not adopt or transport to Canada due to border closings. Please revisit our Petfinders site once the borders open! Thanks for understanding!

Rowdy was found abandoned with two other dogs in a small town in Louisiana.  He was estimated to be 3 to 4 months old at the time.  He is very loving, loyal, and playful.  He plays rough though, and it is recommended he be in an one dog family and/or socialized training with other dogs to learn to play. He plays with other dogs at our rescue currently but very ruff which is how he got his name Ruff Rowdy!!!! LOL.  Honestly with time and training we think he will learn to play at a more acceptable level.

 He is leash walked trained but still a high energy puppy who needs to be taught some manners. He would do better in a home with no kids or older kids in high school.  He gets nervous around loud noises and lets face it, kids are loud!!

At his foster home before coming to the shelter, he was use to being crated at night and free to roam the large fenced in yard during the day.  He was not quite house trained but learning! He really enjoys running long distances, smelling new things and water!! I think he would be great addition to an active family or couple who have an adventurous taste! He loves to run fast and hard and then he comes back happy and panting!! If you think Ruff Rowdy would be the perfect fit for you and your family, please email us at LongJ1003@aol.com and Katybug6067@gmail.com. Thanks for adopting to adopt!!!

animal.description:
*****************************************************************
PLEASE READ THOROUGHLY BEFORE INQUIRING
*****************************************************************

--ABOUT CANDY--
Candy is a sweet little lady with the people she trusts but sour with strangers. She needs a quiet and gentle family with dog savvy kids no younger than 15, if any at all. She will bark when she's upset, so often at strangers and when she feels left out. She wouldn't do well in apartment or multi-family style home as the noise would bother the neighbors, and noisy neighbors would bother her. She's especially scared of strangers touching her, and even of more trusted people picking her up. She may nip when panicked. She bullies cats but does well with sweet and friendly dogs closer to her size that don't mind a little sass. She is housebroken and loves to go for walks; they've been the best way to bond with her. She struggles with stairs and can only do a few steps. This combined with her fear of being picked up means there should be no necessary steps for her to climb in her new home.

Key Notes:
-6-year old spayed female.
-Chihuahua mix.
-16 pounds and slightly overweight.
-Surrendered by extended family to a rescue in Alabama when her elderly owner passed.
-Experience with timid dogs needed.
-No apartments or multi-family homes.
-Okay with dog-savvy kids 15 and up.
-Should not live with cats.
-Good with friendly and submissive dogs with the exception of being good with her long time friend, Nacho.
-No stairs she will need to climb.
-No more than 8 hours alone a day.
-Low-medium energy; loves walks and the occasional run, but happy to laze around.
-Does not like to be picked up; will tolerate after she learns to trust you.
-Will bark when upset (at strangers, when she feels ignored, etc.).
-Housebroken and good on leash; loves walks!

--THE ADOPTION PROCESS--
If you are interested in adopting this animal, please submit an online application. Applications will be reviewed as received. If in our opinion a pet is a good candidate for you, an adoption counselor will contact you to schedule a zoom chat. If you do not hear from us it simply means either the animal has been adopted or we have not received the right pet for you. The application process is at no charge to you and only needs to be completed once as all applications will be kept on file.

Online applications can be found here: www.buddydoghs.com/forms

Check out our FAQ for answers to most questions here: www.buddydoghs.com/faq

Adopters must be at least 21 years of age and a Massachusetts resident.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.All of the animals posted on our site have been temperament tested. While not all are in the immediate area, once we have processed and approved your application, we will move the dog to our adoptive area for you to meet, greet and hopefully adopt. Sometimes we will have more than one application on a dog. That does not mean it automatically goes to another family but you should be aware of the fact that until you are approved and set up for the meet/greet.. the dog could get adopted by another applicant.
Who would love a quiet afternoon with you gardening in the shire and be ready on a moments notice to accompany you on a grand adventure? Samwise, of course! Sam is earnest, rustic almost, and he wears his heart of gold on his sleeve. Sam will look to you to be his leader and he will be the secret strength that carries you though even the toughest of days. His resilient spirit has allowed him to travel from humble beginnings with no place of his own to winning the hearts of the rescue volunteers who have been teaching him the ways of people and the comforts of home. Imagine the joy of never having to feel guilty knowing that your best friend would rather to be home with you than at the dog park.
Sam is now looking for his forever place in the country with a fenced yard, quiet surroundings, and an experienced dog lover who prefers the road less traveled for times when a hike is the order of the day. How much fun will it will be walking the solitary back roads on a Tuesday morning at 10 when everyone else is well... too busy to seize the warm sunny moment you'll share.
Sam is housebroken, crate trained, knows sit, and certainly knows breakfast and dinner routines. He enthusiastically loves to lean-in and he is a first class snuggler who will not be shy about joining you on the sofa to savor a movie or three. Sam is ready for the unconditional love of a friend who will teach him even more about the ways of people. In return he will promise to do his very best to listen to your stories, his eyes meeting yours in agreement that life's journey is difficult and worthy and fun and glorious but not all at once. All the while Sam will share with you the rewards of investing in love.
FENCE REQUIREMENT: Sam is going to need a yard with a privacy fence that is at least 4 foot high.

If you are interested in Sam, please contact:
rorrcanine@gmail.com
*** Click here to sponsor this dog! ***

animal.description:
You can find our Pet Adoption Application at: https://form.jotform.com/90981337198166
 Thank you for your interest in one of our pets for adoption. We take pet ownership seriously. We do our best to make sure the pet you have selected is right for your home.  Please text us at 325-651-0659 or email at jana@newbark.org for more information about this pet.  

Adoption requirements:    
1.  Must be 18 years of age or have approval from a parent or guardian. 

2. Adopters that rent their home must give landlord's information to New Beginnings prior to adoption and permission to have pets will be confirmed.  

3. Before adoption a homecheck may be required.  If adopting out of the San Angelo, Tx we will accept videos of your home and fence as a home check. 
 
4. All dogs are up to date on rabies, parvo and distemper vaccinations, microchipped and spayed/neutered. A vet reference may be asked for prior to adoption.  

Adoption fee: $200

animal.description:
Stella Rose, what a pretty little girl! she is, young was 1 yr old on Nov. 5th 2020.  She is a whopping 14 lbs 6 oz!! full of love, excitement and energy.  Stella is very playful, good with all people, and children.  She is well behaved and good mannered. We prefer a home with no other animals but a home with a young MALE dog to play with her is a possibility. 

Apartment life is not the right fit for this girl, she is like a watch dog and will bark at strange noises and people to let you know someone is too close to your home. Right now she spends too much time in her crate because her mom works and the other dogs she lives with are seniors and they don't want to be bothered. A fenced yard would be great too, but not mandatory.  Stella is very much like a JRT, she is full of energy, very playful but does like to cuddle too. 

Stella has what is called dry eye in her left eye.  It does not require surgery.
It requires eye drops twice daily and  Artificial Tears should be done as often as possible.

Reach out to AFEW if you would like more information.  Her adoption fee is $300.  She is spayed and has all her vaccinations.

Note: AFEW reserves the right to deny any application that is deemed unfit or unsuitable for the animal. Please be aware that our animal adoptions are NOT on a first come- first serve basis. Our sole purpose is to find the best possible home for the animals that fall under our care.

Complete an online application at http://afewpets.org/machform/view.php?id=4 and email it to afew_pets@comcast.net

A healthy pet is a happy pet! Protect your pet's health with Healthy Paws Pet Insurance and save up to 90% on your vet bills visit http://www.healthypawspetinsurance.com for your free quote (use code AFEW for a special discount) and learn how your protected pet helps save more homeless pets!
